content.html:
AE BKT


Use · SHOOTING SETTING > AE BKT SETTING to choose the
bracketing amount, bracketing order, and number of shots. Each
time the shutter button is pressed, the camera will take the spec-
ified number of shots: one using the metered value for exposure
and the others over- or under-exposed by multiples of the select-
ed bracketing amount.

Regardless of the bracketing amount, exposure will not exceed the
limits of the exposure metering system.

FILM SIMULATION BKT


Each time the shutter is released, the camera takes one shot and
processes it to create copies with different film simulation settings,
chosen using � SHOOTING SETTING > FILM SIMULATION BKT.

DR DYNAMIC RANGE BKT


5

Each time the shutter button is pressed, the camera takes three
shots with different dynamic ranges: 100% for the first, 200% for
the second, and 400% for the third.

While dynamic range bracketing is in effect, sensitivity will be restrict-
ed to a minimum of ISO 640; the sensitivity previously in effect is re-
stored when bracketing ends.
